kend\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed description for the Schema worker. Include: file name, all Pydantic BaseModel classes with validation, and example data.\"\n    }},\n    {{\n      \"task_id\": \"endpoints\",\n      \"group\": \"backend\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed description for the Endpoints worker. Include: file name, all FastAPI route handlers, HTTP methods, path/query params, request/response models, and CORS setup.\"\n    }},\n    {{\n      \"task_id\": \"tests\",\n      \"group\": \"backend\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed description for the Tests worker. Include: file name, test functions for every endpoint, fixtures, and edge-case coverage.\"\n    }}\n  ]\n}}\n\n## Rules\n- ALWAYS produce exactly 6 subtasks: 3 frontend (html, css, js) + 3 backend (schema, endpoints, tests).\n- task_id MUST be one of: html, css, js, schema, endpoints, tests.\n- group MUST be either \"frontend\" or \"backend\".\n- The JS description MUST reference the backend API endpoints (URL, method, payload shape) so the frontend and backend integrate correctly.\n- Descriptions must be specific, self-contained, and actionable.\n- Include explicit file names in each description.\n- NEVER output markdown fences or extra text — only the JSON object.\n\n## Blackboard Registration\nAfter you finish, your subtasks are automatically posted to the system blackboard so the Orchestrator can track them.\n\n## User Request\na landing page for a multy vatimaing with img's", "meta": {}}
